title: Paris Review editor says new Houellebecq book misunderstood
text: > Entertainment Paris Review editor says new Houellebecq book misunderstood FOR STORY SLUGGED EU BOOKS HOULLEBECQ SUBMISSION BY GREG KELLER - This Wednesday, Jan. 7, 2015 photo shows French novelist Michel Houellebecq after an interview on radio station France Inter, in Paris. The latest novel by Michel Houellebecq, the bad boy of French letters, has been called everything from an Islamophobic rant to a “French literary suicide.” Imagining the election of a Muslim president in France, “Submission” struck a raw nerve when it came out this year on the same day as the Charlie Hebdo attacks in Paris. (AP Photo/Thibault Camus)
